Package: ctwas
Type: Package
Title: Adjusting for genetic confounders in transcriptome-wide association studies 
  improves discovery of risk genes of complex traits
Date: 2024-02-05
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R: c(person("Siming","Zhao",role="aut",email="siming.zhao06@gmail.com"),
             person("Wesley","Crouse",role="aut"),
             person("Sheng","Qian",role=c("aut", "cre"),email="shengqian@uchicago.edu"),
             person("Kaixuan","Luo",role="aut",email="kevinlkx@gmail.com"),
             person("Matthew","Stephens",role="aut"),
             person("Xin","He",role="aut"))
Description: This package implements the causal-TWAS (cTWAS) method we developed to identify
  causal genes in GWAS. It is a generalization of Transcriptome-wide association studies (TWAS), 
  but when analyzing any gene, it adjusts for other nearby genes and all nearby genetic variants.
URL: https://github.com/xinhe-lab/ctwas
BugReports: https://github.com/xinhe-lab/ctwas/issues
